h3. Ingredients

* 1 cup red lentils
* 2 cups water
* 1/2 Onion
* 2 tomatoes (chopped up)
* 1 tsp cumin powder
* 1/2 tsp chilli powder
* 1/2 tsp coriander
* 1/2 tsp ginger (if you got it!)
* salt
* water

h3. Method
# Fry chopped onion in a small sauce(not frying)pan for a bit adding the spices as you fry.
# Add water and lentils (enough water so that the lentils are covered) and turn down heat.
# Add tomatoes and simmer until lentils are soft (add more or less water if you like them more runny or thick).
# Salt to taste.

Serves 3.

h3. Options
# Add extra vegies. Carrot. Celery. Split Peas. Potato?
